+/*
+ * NTARI OS — Cyclone DDS musl libc thread stack size patch
+ *
+ * Problem:
+ *   musl libc default thread stack size is 128 KB (vs. glibc's 2–10 MB).
+ *   Cyclone DDS internal threads — particularly those handling DDS
+ *   serialization, discovery (SPDP/SEDP), and transport — can overflow
+ *   the 128 KB default when processing complex QoS types or large
+ *   discovery bursts.
+ *
+ * Fix:
+ *   When building on musl libc (detected via __MUSL__ or absence of
+ *   __GLIBC__), set minimum thread stack size to 2 MB before spawning
+ *   any Cyclone DDS internal thread.
+ *
+ * Upstream issue:
+ *   No upstream fix exists. This patch must be reapplied on each
+ *   Cyclone DDS version update until upstreamed.
+ *
+ * Tested against: Cyclone DDS 0.10.x / 0.11.x (Jazzy-era)
+ * Platform:       Alpine Linux 3.23 (musl libc 1.2.5)
+ * Author:         NTARI OS project
+ */
+
 /*
